heading.emphasis:
Osbornellus aielloae Domínguez & Godoy
, sp. nov.

subSubSection.paragraph:
Description. Length: 5.5–6.9 mm . Member of the
O. auronitens
group ( Figs 1a ). General description as in
O. eberhardi
.

Diagnosis. Very similar to
O. anonae
in appearance, but in ventral view the aedeagus of
O. aielloae
has the ventral processes wider and more divergent at the apices. In
O. anonae
the ventral processes are narrow and slightly divergent.
Distribution. Known from Costa Rica and Panama ; 1–3000 m .
Etymology. This species is named in honor of Annette Aiello for the loan of specimens and her help in obtaining type specimens.
